File: Archbishop Emeritus Desmond Tutu. JOHANNESBURG - Archbishop Emeritus Desmond Tutu has been discharged from hospital, the Desmond & Leah Tutu Legacy Foundation has announced on Monday. Tutu spent six days in a Cape Town hospital, receiving treatment for a recurring infection. READ: Tutu hospitalised for 'stubborn' infection The 88-year-old Nobel Peace Prize laureate has been treated for the condition several times in the past few years. The family has thanked everyone who's sent love and prayers.